PILOT STUDY 1¶

Metadata¶

  • the online survey was conducted on July 11, 2023
  • the survey included both quantitative as well as qualitative questions
  • participants were Bachlor (?) students from FH Potsdam's xxx course who filled in the course as their homework assignment
  • sample size n=24
  • survey was provided both in English as well as in German language (caveat: with two examples not being fully provided in German)
  • the survey was conducted online, using TU Dortmund's Limesurvey platform
  • when exporting the data, yes and no answers were coded numerically, with yes == 1and no == 2

Objectives¶

1) to get an estimate completion time in order to decide whether it is a reasonable / appropriate effort to ask of survey participants and

2) to understand if the presentation of examples and phrasing of questions needs further refinement for the representative surve

3) to obtain first indications if the number of dimensions of a chart correlates in any way with participants' understanding of charts and their insights gained

4) to reassess if the selected method to classify and evaluate participants' responses is feasible and appropriate way for evaluating and interpreting the data

# in original_format as GROUP1:
# Find anything of unedfined length 
# until the first [ 
# followed by a capital letter of undefined length
# followed by a number of any length
# followed by a ]_
# as GROUP2:
# anything of any length

original_format= '(.*\[[A-Z]*\d*\])_(.*)'
# GROUP2 equals the question text
target_format_questionText='\g<2>'
question_texts_list = [re.sub(original_format, target_format_questionText, column_title) for column_title in questionCodes_questionTexts_list]

# GROUP1 
target_format_questionCode='\g<1>'

# First round of cleaning column titles
question_codes_interimslist = [re.sub(original_format, target_format_questionCode, column_title) for column_title in questionCodes_questionTexts_list]

# Second round of cleaning column titles
interims_format= '(\d*)(\_.*)'
target_format_questionCode2= '\g<1>'
question_codes_cleanedlist= [re.sub(interims_format,target_format_questionCode2,interimquestioncode) for interimquestioncode in question_codes_interimslist]

Overview of analysis questions¶

General assessment¶

  • [x] What was the overall completion time for the survey?
  • [x] What was the time needed for evaluation & insight tasks?
  • [x] What is the overall visual literacy assessment of the sample group?
  • [x] Is there a representative represenation (some sort of consensus) of the ranking of chart types?
  • [x] What is the sociodemographic description of the sample?

Evaluation of examples¶

  • [x] Is there a representative represenation (some sort of consensus) of the evaluation (with regards to liking, understanding, insightful) of examples?
  • [ ] Does the evaluation of charts (with regards to liking, understanding, insightful) correlate with topic interest indicated by participants?
  • [x] Are charts with higher dimensionality perceived differently (with regards to liking, understanding, insightful) from charts with lower dimensionality?
  • [x] Does the evaluation of charts (with regards to liking, understanding, insightful) correlate with self-assessed visual literacy?

Insights from examples¶

  • [ ] What kinds of insights were generated by participants? (as classified by Lee et al. (2017) / Boy et al. (2014)/ Burns et al. (2020) and Stokes & Hearst (2022) based on framework of Lundgard & Satyanarayan (2022))
  • [ ] Do charts with a higher dimensionality allow for more insights (number of insights) or deeper insights (different qualitative levels as classified by SH/LS(2022) framework)?
  • [ ] Does the number of insights or quality of insights correlate with self-assessed visual literacy?
  • [ ] Does the number of insights or quality of insights correlate with evaluation of charts (with regards to liking, understanding, insightful)? I.e. more insights/deeper insight for charts that were liked / better understood/deemed insightful

Memorability of examples¶

  • [x] What chart examples were mentioned in the remembering question?
  • [x] Does the remembering correlate to dimensionality of the charts?
  • [x] What are mentioned reasons for remembering a chart?

timings_list = []

for participant in set(participant_example_df_melted['id']):
    
    participant_timings_dict={}# creating empty dict to store data
    
    # getting example ids for each participant
    ex2=participant_example_df_melted[(participant_example_df_melted['id']==participant)&(participant_example_df_melted['variable']=='gleichunga')]['value'].item()
    ex3=participant_example_df_melted[(participant_example_df_melted['id']==participant)&(participant_example_df_melted['variable']=='gleichungb')]['value'].item()
    ex4=participant_example_df_melted[(participant_example_df_melted['id']==participant)&(participant_example_df_melted['variable']=='gleichungc')]['value'].item()

    #constructing column names to look up times
    try:
        columnname2dbsp = 'Beispiel'+str(int(ex2))+'Time'
        columnname3dbsp = 'Beispiel'+str(int(ex3))+'Time'
        columnname4dbsp = 'Beispiel'+str(int(ex4))+'Time'

        columnname2dins = 'ErkBsp'+str(int(ex2))+'Time'
        columnname3dins = 'ErkBsp'+str(int(ex3))+'Time'
        columnname4dins = 'ErkBsp'+str(int(ex4))+'Time'
    except:
        pass
    
    # looking up time each participant used for each example, both for the evalation of the example as well as the insight task
    particpant_df_temp = df_re[df_re['id']==participant]
    time_2d_ex = particpant_df_temp[columnname2dbsp].item()
    time_3d_ex = particpant_df_temp[columnname3dbsp].item()
    time_4d_ex = particpant_df_temp[columnname4dbsp].item()

    time_2d_ins = particpant_df_temp[columnname2dins].item()
    time_3d_ins = particpant_df_temp[columnname3dins].item()
    time_4d_ins = particpant_df_temp[columnname4dins].item()
    
    # adding everything to dict    
    participant_timings_dict['id']=participant
    participant_timings_dict['example2d']=ex2
    participant_timings_dict['example3d']=ex3
    participant_timings_dict['example4d']=ex4
    participant_timings_dict['example2d_t_ex']=time_2d_ex
    participant_timings_dict['example3d_t_ex']=time_3d_ex
    participant_timings_dict['example4d_t_ex']=time_4d_ex
    participant_timings_dict['example2d_t_ins']=time_2d_ins
    participant_timings_dict['example3d_t_ins']=time_3d_ins
    participant_timings_dict['example4d_t_ins']=time_4d_ins
